            <title>[JCR-1759] Simplify the usage of OCM annotations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1759</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>If we are using more reflections during the OCM init phase (class descriptor loading), some OCM annotation settings are not necessary : &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
@Node(isAbtract=true) : used to specify an abstract classes&lt;br/&gt;
@Node(extend=....) : used to specify the ancestor class&lt;br/&gt;
@Node(isInterface= ...) : used to specify the entity as an interface&lt;br/&gt;
@implement  : used to specify the associated interfaces&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If this refactoring is done, we can set them as deprecated.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The performances will not suffer because this is done only once during the application startup (when the ObjectContentManager is initialized). </description>
